{"key":"processedPost-13977738","value":{"id":13977738,"first":13840981,"last":13983452,"when":1297951382,"utime":"02/17/11 04:03 PM","cleanedPost":"If one has a method of keeping the bulk substrate sterile until fully colonized, sterilization is fine.&nbsp; In fact, I sterilize coffee, rice bran, and straw/hay in my bulk shiitake substrates, but they're colonized in filter patch bags and remain sterile until removed.<br />TerryM, pure coffee grinds will work for oysters, but mixing with some straw or sawdust will yield much better.&nbsp; Coffee is a great supplement, but really needs some other material for best results.&nbsp; I know of one oyster farmer who collects coffee grinds along with the paper filters from IHOP/Denney's type restaurants and uses those together with pretty good results.<br />RR"}}